snippet.textDisplay:
Of course she’s gorgeous to look at (I believe it’s spiritual to a degree ), and many of the comments here may just be coming from a place of jealousy and hatred, but I think I can speak for myself and some other Christians, when I say that what is so repulsive about this, is their a idolization/worship of each other while claiming to follow Jesus. Posting Christ’s name Or a bible verse on insta sometimes doesn't make them disciples of Christ. They are misleading many by not obeying the Gospel. They go to church to get their ears tickled, and I’m almost positive they have no accountability and would never receive any real conviction about what they’re portraying to the world. What it means to follow Jesus for real. They are not displaying the truth of what it means to be a disciple on their enormous platform, they know it would cost them EVERYTHING.
It’s like they’re saying Jesus out of one side of their mouth and then displaying totally inappropriate behavior, doing inappropriate photo shoots that are lustful in nature etc. The focus of these two, is like Hollywood’s, is all wrong, just like the church bodies they’re a part of. That’s a whole other conversation.
I believe this is one of the biggest, most powerful false movements that is dragging away Christians and nonbelievers alike. And somebody needs to confront it. Repent Bieber’s, Repent. ✌️✌🏽
